@startuml dms_attention_to_hwp_driver_monitor_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title DMS Attention To HWP Driver Monitor Signal Flow\n(DMS/attention context -> HWP driver-monitor request and availability)

participant "DMS / cruise /\nlane-guide context" as DmsCtx #F4F7FB
participant "HWP\nhighway pilot owner" as HWP #E8F7E8
participant "Pilot state bus" as PilotBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / panels" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Driver Monitoring Inputs ==

DmsCtx -> HWP : dmsActive\nattentionLevel\ncruiseState\nlaneGuideState\nnavRouteClass
HWP -> HWP : if dmsInputStale then\ndmsActive = 1 / attentionLevel = 3
HWP -> HWP : highwayReady =\n(navRouteClass == 2 and cruiseState >= 1 and attentionLevel <= 2)
HWP -> HWP : driverMonitorReq =\n(dmsActive == 1 and attentionLevel >= 2)
HWP -> HWP : availabilityLevel reduced when driverMonitorReq == 1
note right of HWP
Representative gating inputs
- dmsActive
- attentionLevel
- cruiseState / laneGuideState
- navRouteClass
end note

== Pilot Publish ==

HWP -> PilotBus : frmHighwayPilotStateMsg\nDriverMonitorReq / AvailabilityLevel
HWP -> PilotBus : HighwayPilotReady / LongCtrlActive / LatCtrlActive
note right of HWP
Representative outputs
- DriverMonitorReq
- AvailabilityLevel
- HighwayPilotReady
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

PilotBus -> Obs : pilot-monitoring readback /\navailability indication

note over DmsCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. DMS and attention context reach HWP
2. HWP decides whether driver monitoring must be enforced
3. HWP publishes monitoring demand and availability level
4. Observers expose pilot availability under driver-monitor conditions
end note

@enduml
